cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.DB

This paper discusses a blockchain-based system for collaborative machine learning, which involves data privacy and ownership. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on training machine learning models. The paper also discusses the use of cloud resources, which falls under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper involves data management and storage, which could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases).
